  "texts": [
    "They are what an agent must do if she is to do anything at all.",
    "Memorably described by one commentator as a \"metaphysical containment wall\" that \"preserve[s] the separate jurisdictions of the mind of the acting subject and what merely happens\" (Lavin, 2013, p. 274), it is these basic actions that lead to trouble for HEC.",
    "What follows is a Davidsonian argument: first, that the cognitive actions involved in offloading are non-basic; second, that non-basic actions are composed only of basic actions and non-actions.",
    "The conclusion of this argument is that the kind of environmental resources appealed to by HEC's supporters cannot be constitutive of the cognitive processes that offloading seems to make available.",
    "Using the A-D Principle as a template, we can introduce an intentional action type to cover the uses of physical action involved in cognitive offloading:"
